<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="522" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,438,933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Remarks.</emphasis>
This widespread, large and diverse genus is distinguished from other members of the tribe by its usually dark appearance dorsally and forewing being usually truncate or concave apically and sometimes distinctly expanded from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[488,571,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[195,1397,191,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[177,1410,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. External features of Mileewa species. a–d, M. clavata sp. nov., a, habitus, dorsal view; b, habitus, lateral view; c, face; d, forewing; e–h, M. rubricosta sp. nov., e, habitus, dorsal view; f, habitus, lateral view; g, face; h, forewing; i–l, forewings, i, M. xiaofeiae; j, M. lackstripa; k, M. houhensis; l, M. alara. Scale lines = 500 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4640629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4640629/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
). Among the Chinese species, the distinction between a rounded or truncate forewing apex is sometimes less clear (see figs 1h-j) while in two other Chinese species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang, Meng &amp; He" authorityYear="2014" box="[1132,1280,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mileewa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="houhensis">
<emphasis box="[1132,1155,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1168,1280,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">houhensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="1998" box="[1332,1430,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mileewa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alara">
<emphasis box="[1332,1355,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1369,1430,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">alara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is distinctly rounded (see figs 1k, 1l) and in the former the head is much narrower than other congeners suggesting it may belong to a different genus. Fifty-six species of 
<taxonomicName box="[779,875,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mileewa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,875,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Mileewa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1142,691,717]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">China</collectingCountry>
(see Appendix) including the three new species described below. As one of the new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="He &amp; Yan &amp; Yang &amp; Webb, 2021" authorityName="He &amp; Yan &amp; Yang &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2021" box="[929,1163,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mileewa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinquemaculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[929,952,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[969,1163,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">quinquemaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1173,1265,727,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1173,1265,727,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, lacks pygofer processes found in other congeners it is only tentatively included in the genus (see under species Remarks). The identity of specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[548,813,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mileewa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margheritae">
<emphasis box="[548,571,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[586,723,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">margheritae</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[995,1062,799,825]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, M. F. &amp; Meng, Z. H. &amp; Li, Z. Z." box="[1078,1386,799,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" refId="ref9057" refString="Yang, M. F., Meng, Z. H. &amp; Li, Z. Z. (2017) Hemiptera: Cicadellidae (II): Cicadellinae. Fauna Sinica: Insecta. Vol. 67. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 1 - 637." type="book" year="2017">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[1146,1196,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">et al</emphasis>
., 2017: 390-394
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 222) needs to be confirmed as specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[711,759,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<collectingCountry box="[862,923,835,862]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">India</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1064,835,861]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
have a slightly different aedeagal shape (Viraktamath &amp; Webb, in prep. and 
<bibRefCitation author="Chiang, C. C. &amp; Knight, W. J." box="[631,1009,871,897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" pagination="117 - 124" refId="ref7263" refString="Chiang, C. C. &amp; Knight, W. J. (1991) Mileewanini of Taiwan. Journal of Taiwan Museum, 44, 117 - 124." type="journal article" year="1991">Chiang &amp; Knight, 1991: 119-121</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 1, respectively) which may have implications for the identity of its junior synonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura. See" authorityName="Matsumura. See" authorityYear="1912" box="[717,1175,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Tylozygoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artemisiae">
<emphasis box="[717,986,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Tylozygoides artemisiae</emphasis>
Matsumura. See
</taxonomicName>
also Notes below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
